<p class="EnTeteTranscription">McKenzie, Alexander. Journal of Great Bear Lake, 1805-1806. An electronic transcription. MFTP #0006</p><div class="ContenuPage">
<p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="fw" style="text-decoration:underline;">1805</span>
</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">he was left to amuse himself all night a long side his fier which he made with his Gun<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[T]</span>he two other Cannoes arrived at 9 O Clock<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Octb<sup>r</sup> 3</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="AddHand-editors">[A]</span>t 5 O Clock in the morning I embarked and two miles above my encampment I Crossed on the S. side of the River to Embark M<sup>r</sup> G.  <span class="AddHand-editors">[H]</span>is trousers were much tore By the Branches and had passed a very disagreeable night as it was very Cold<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  I put him a shore on the N. side of the River as his Cannoe remained at the Camp to Gum<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[A]</span>t 8 O Clock encamped at the half way point between the Rappids &amp; Bear Lake<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">4<sup>th</sup></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Embarked at 5 O Clock and arrived at Great Bear Lake Castle at 4 O Clock in the afternoon my Cannoe only.  I was in the House before they perceived me.  I found seven Indians at the Fort of which not one was able to kill a Carriboux<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">5<sup>th</sup></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">M<sup>r</sup> H. &amp; G. arrived at 9 O Clock in the morning.  I made up M<sup>r</sup> Henrys Equipment to send him to Bear Island as I found it would have been imprudent to send him to the <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Lushues</span> not having a hunter for him nor a man or Indian that had been there<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>   Sansols was with the Red Knives on their lands and had not been to the Lushue Countrie in the Summer as was expected<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">6<sup>th</sup></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="AddHand-editors">[A]</span>t 8 O Clock in the morning M<sup>r</sup> H. embarked for his post with 5 men one woman and a Indian with orders not to make any Credits and as soon as the hunt was over to send the yallow or Red Knives to Mountain Island and if he met Sansols and the Indians that was with him not to trade with them but to take what provisions he might want and give them a order on me for the amount<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[A]</span> great fall of snow to day and very cold<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">7<sup>th</sup></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">I gave a few Credits to the Indians and sent them from the fort<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[D]</span>elivered the Summer men their Equipment &amp;ca<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">8<sup>th</sup></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;"><span class="AddHand-editors">[S]</span>et the men to Build a Small House as the present one is not fit to pass the winter<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[S]</span>now and Strong N. wind<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>

<p align="page-number"><span class="AddHand-editors">[4]</span></p>

